On Wednesday, the state of Vermont <a href="https://legislature.vermont.gov/Documents/2020/Docs/BILLS/H-0057/H-0057%20As%20Introduced.pdf">held hearings</a> on a proposed amendment to the state's constitution that would create a state constitutional right to unrestricted abortion.

The amendment states that "[e]very individual who becomes pregnant has the fundamental right to choose to carry a pregnancy to term, give birth to a child, or to have an abortion." The amendment also forbids public entities from restricting access to abortion. Under the proposed amendment, "[n]o State or local law enforcement shall prosecute any individual for inducing, performing, or attempting to induce or perform the individual's own abortion."

